00:07:08.750 --> 00:07:10.655
So this is basically how you can

00:07:10.655 --> 00:07:13.325
override your symbols content.

00:07:13.325 --> 00:07:15.170
The last thing I'm
going to talk about

00:07:15.170 --> 00:07:17.915
is unlinking your symbols.

00:07:17.915 --> 00:07:19.775
How can you unlink symbol?

00:07:19.775 --> 00:07:20.990
There are times that you want to

00:07:20.990 --> 00:07:22.670
make some changes and you want

00:07:22.670 --> 00:07:25.745
these changes to be applied
to specific elements,

00:07:25.745 --> 00:07:27.515
okay, to do that first,

00:07:27.515 --> 00:07:29.840
select your symbol,
Right-click on it.

00:07:29.840 --> 00:07:33.275
And from here you can
find link instance.

00:07:33.275 --> 00:07:35.375
If you click on
Edit main symbol,

00:07:35.375 --> 00:07:37.670
you will be taken to
the master symbol

00:07:37.670 --> 00:07:39.335
and you will be able to edit it.

00:07:39.335 --> 00:07:42.590
But if you unlink
instance just like that,

00:07:42.590 --> 00:07:45.170
now, it's just a simple div.

00:07:45.170 --> 00:07:47.990
As you can see, it's
no longer a symbol.

00:07:47.990 --> 00:07:50.990
And you can recognize that
from the Navigator because

00:07:50.990 --> 00:07:54.875
here the icon of these
symbols is green.

00:07:54.875 --> 00:07:58.205
But this is just a
simple div block.

00:07:58.205 --> 00:08:01.895
Now, if I change the
dimension of this image,

00:08:01.895 --> 00:08:05.795
this change is unique to
this particular card,

